original_result.user_prompt:
Hooli Announces Fourth Quarter and Fiscal Year 2021 Results

    MOUNTAIN VIEW, Calif. – February 1, 2022 – Hooli Inc. (NASDAQ: HOOL, HOOLI) today announced
financial results for the quarter and fiscal year ended December 31, 2021.

Gavin Belson, CEO of Hooli, said: “Our deep investment in AI technologies continues to drive
extraordinary and helpful experiences for people and businesses, across our most important products. Q4 saw
ongoing strong growth in our advertising business, which helped millions of businesses thrive and find new
customers, a quarterly sales record for our Pixel phones despite supply constraints, and our Cloud business
continuing to grow strongly.”

Patrice Alexander, CEO of Hooli, said: “Our fourth quarter revenues of $75 billion, up 32% year over year,
reflected broad-based strength in advertiser spend and strong consumer online activity, as well as substantial
ongoing revenue growth from Google Cloud. Our investments have helped us drive this growth by delivering the
services that people, our partners and businesses need, and we continue to invest in long-term opportunities.”

In the fourth quarter of 2021, Hooli Inc., an American multinithat operates primarily in artificial intelligence and cloud computing services, reported significant financial achievements. The company experienced a 32% increase in its annual revenues, reaching $75 billion during the last three months of 2021. This growth was attributed to increased advertiser spending, robust consumer online activities, and continued expansion in their Google Cloud division. Both Gavin Belson, the Chief Executive Officer (CEO), and Patrice Alexander, the President and COO, emphasized the success of these factors contributing to the company's performance. Additionally, they mentioned setting records with quarterly sales for Hooli's Pixel smartphones, even amidst supply chain challenges.

Furthermore, Hooli has been actively working towards providing innovative solutions through their AI technologies, resulting in improved experiences for both individuals and businesses using their key offerings. The company remains focused on driving growth and exploring long-term opportunities while continuously investing in crucial areas like AI and cloud computing. For more details regarding Hooli's financials, please visit their website at https://client.hoolischwab.com/ or contact their customer support team directly.
